result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Jennifer E Carrick in court with attorney Acalia Halverson. Elizabeth R. Constable appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
11:20 a.m.  Court calls the cases. 
All cases heard: 15CF186, 15CM60, 15CM126, 15CM222

Plea questionnaire/Agreement filed.
Prosecutor states plea agreement.
Attorney for Defendant concurs with agreement stated.

Defendant enters a plea of: 
15CF186 Counts 1 thru 3 - NO CONTEST
15CM126 Count 1 - NO CONTEST
15CM60 Counts 1 & 2 - NO CONTEST

Court questions Defendant regarding plea.
Court informs Defendant of Constitutional Rights. Court advises Defendant of Elements State must prove for the Charge.
Court questions Attorney for Defendant.
Defendant and Atty Halverson agree the defendant qualifies as a repeat offender for each of these offenses. 
Court finds Defendant's Plea is freely, voluntarily and intelligently made.
Attorneys stipulate that there is factual basis for the charge(s).

BY THE COURT:
Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charge(s).
Court finds the defendant guilty 15CF186 Counts 1 thru 3, 15CM126 Count 1, 15CM60 Counts 1 & 2 including the repeat offender provision.  Clerk directed to enter Judgment of Conviction this date.

No victims are present. 
Atty Constable makes sentencing arguments to the Court. 
Atty Halverson makes sentencing arguments to the Court. 
Defendant makes statements to the Court. 
Court questions the defendant. 

BY THE COURT:  
15CM126 Count 2 and 15CM222 in its entirety are dismissed and read-in. 

15CF186 Count 1 - 
Sentence withheld. 
Placed on probation for a period of 3 years: 
Pay restitution of $1,722.58.  Pay at a rate of $100 per month.  
Maintain fulltime employment.  During periods of umemployment, do 5 job contacts per week until she gets employment. 
AODA & comply with treatment recommendations.
Maintain absolute sobriety. 
Do not possess or consume alcohol or be on premises where alcohol is served/sold as its primary business except within scope of your employment.
Do not possess/consume controlled substances without a valid prescription and be taken according to the prescription. 
Do not possess any drug paraphernalia. 
Do not associate with any persons possessing or consuming controlled substances.
Not to assoicate with persons who are on probation or extended supervision without the express consent of her agent without prior approval. 
No contact with Shopko, Menards & JR Liquor or be upon their premises. 
Pay costs including the DNA surcharge & restitution surcharges. 

15CF186 Count 2 - 
Sentence withheld.
Placed on probation for a period of 2 years, concurrent:
Comply with all conditions set forth in Count 1. 
Pay costs including the DNA surcharge. 

15CF186 Count 3 - 
Sentence withheld.
Placed on probation for a period of 2 years, concurrent:
Comply with all conditions set forth in Count 1. 
Pay costs including the DNA surcharge. 

Court finds there is no credit on this case at this time. 

15CM126  Count 1 - 
60 days jail. 
59 days credit. 
Pay costs including the DNA surcharge.   To be paid within 60 days or set up a payment plan. 

15CM60 Count 1 -
Sentence withheld.  
2 days credit if revoked. 
Placed on probation for a period of 2 years, concurrent. 
Comply with all conditions in 15CF186. 
Pay costs including the DNA surcharge. 

15CM60 Count 2 -
Sentence withheld. 
Placed on probation for a period of 2 years, concurrent. 
Comply with all conditions in 15CF186 Count 1. 
Pay costs including the DNA surcharge.

Do not have direct/indirect contact with the following persons/places:  Shopko in Plover
Remanded to Portage County Sheriff until bond is posted.

Amended 6/1/15:  Not to be on the premises of JR Liquor. 
Bond now covers 15CF186 & 15CM222.

Attorney Acalia Halverson in court, defendant Jennifer E Carrick not in court, in custody. David R. Knaapen appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant Jennifer E Carrick appeared by video. Prosecuting Atty David R. Knaapen appeared for State of Wisconsin.

Both files heard: 15CF186, 15CM222

Attorney/Defendant received copy of criminal complaints.
Court informs defendant of charges and maximum penalties.
Attorney/Defendant waives reading of complaints.

Atty Knaapen isn't sure if bond was set in the CM case.  Bond was set in 15CF186. 
Court questions Atty Halverson. 

BY THE COURT:  Bond continued.  

NOT GUILTY pleas entered in 15CM222.

BY THE COURT:  Bond now covers both files 15CF186 and 15CM222.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for June 22, 2015 at 03:00 pm.  Status conference scheduled for June 22, 2015 at 03:00 pm.
